Siano date, per 
\begin_inset Formula $i=1,2,\dots,N$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{i}\in L^{p_{i}}(\mu)$
\end_inset

, dove 
\begin_inset Formula $1\leq p_{i}\leq\infty$
\end_inset

.
 Mostrare che 
\begin_inset Formula $f=f_{1}f_{2}\cdots f_{N}\in L^{p}(\mu)$
\end_inset

, dove:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{p}=\frac{1}{p_{1}}+\frac{1}{p_{2}}+\cdots+\frac{1}{p_{N}},
\]

