\begin_layout Solution*
Chiaramente la tesi segue, per induzione, dal caso 
\begin_inset Formula $N=2$
\end_inset

.
 In tal caso, dalla disuguaglianza di Holder si ha:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left\Vert f\right\Vert _{p}^{p} & =\intop_{X}\left|f_{1}\right|^{\frac{p_{1}p_{2}}{p_{1}+p_{2}}}\left|f_{2}\right|^{\frac{p_{1}p_{2}}{p_{1}+p_{2}}}\,\text{d}\mu\\
 & \leq\left\{ \intop_{X}\left|f_{1}\right|^{p_{1}}\text{d}\mu\right\} ^{\frac{p_{2}}{p_{1}+p_{2}}}\left\{ \intop_{X}\left|f_{2}\right|^{p_{2}}\text{d}\mu\right\} ^{\frac{p_{1}}{p_{1}+p_{2}}}\\
 & =\left\Vert f_{1}\right\Vert _{p_{1}}^{p}\left\Vert f_{2}\right\Vert _{p_{2}}^{p}.
\end{align*}

